wondering if anybody could help me. The story would have a plot sort of like a micheal chrichton or clive cussler novel. I've been trying to think of something but I can't. All ideas would be greatly appreciated. Can somebody please help me! <p><img src=http://www.envy.nu/cprodigy/sig1.gif.gif>
<-o0prodigy studios0o-> </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uchildprodigy11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>childprodigy11</A> at: 5/14/02 12:10:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uben2theedge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ben2theEdge</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/14/02 12:55:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Ermm...</span><hr size=1> Can you be a little more specific? Writing a story is really easy if you know the right steps. All you really have to do is answer a couple questions.<br>
<br>
1. What's the genre? (Action, sci-fi, horror, combo, etc.)<br>
<br>
2. When/Where does the story take place?<br>
<br>
3. Who/what is the antagonist? (Villian)<br>
<br>
4. What are the motives of the antagonist?<br>
<br>
5. Who are the protagonists? (Good guys)<br>
<br>
6. How do the protagonists become involved?<br>
<br>
From there you need to come up with some trademark situations -- something or anything that hasn't been done before. Then string those together in a chronological order. Then figure out how those trademark situations affect the characters, and that's it in a nutshell.<br>
<br>
If you need help though, you'll have to be able to answer at least the first two questions on that list. Otherwise it's like searching for a needle in a haystack. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uchildprodigy11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>childprodigy11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/15/02 12:11:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with plot, please help me!</span><hr size=1> well..... The plot is sorta action/adventure and has someting to do with either discovering something new from the past that will change the world or creating something new that will change the world. I haven't decided. <br>
      It would take place in present times but I haven't decided where though. <br>
                 Will that help? <p><img src=http://www.envy.nu/cprodigy/sig1.gif.gif>
<-o0prodigy studios0o-> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/18/02 8:38:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No way dude</span><hr size=1> So the only thing you won't be needing help on is that you know he discovers something that changes the world? Wait you even seem a bit confused on that one little bit.<br>
<br>
I would be glad to help. But, Bob helps those who help themselves. I don't mean to sound stuck up or anything like that but, I don't think anyone just wants to give you a story. Why don't you lay a basic foundation. Know your characters know at least the most bare-bones basic plot. Know what time you're in. That has a lot to do with the plot. Figure out if he's discovering or creating. Those are two entirely different things that can change your main character by a very wide margin. Either he's a super scientist or super explorer. <br>
<br>
After you can show that you've put a bit more thought into it I'll be glad to help in any way that I can. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uchildprodigy11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>childprodigy11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/18/02 4:32:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: need help with plot, please help me!</span><hr size=1> Thanks. you have given me some things I should think about. almost everything I do, the plot is given to me so I'm new to plot making.<br>
       Anyways, here is the start of my plot.<br>
<br>
setting:2002 (present) Partly in germany and in america<br>
<br>
Main character: His name is Corbin Johnson and he works for the government(american) as a spy(maybe CIA).<br>
<br>
Storyline: It mainly has to do with Corbin and the agency that he works for finding out that hitler was creating some sort of mutants or &quot;super humans&quot; during world war 2. These mutants still live in germany and are bent on fufilling hitler's goals. Most of it is the gornment trying to stop these mutants which is what I need the most help with. <p><img src=http://www.envy.nu/cprodigy/sig1.gif.gif>
<-o0prodigy studios0o-> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uascendedbob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ascended Bob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/19/02 12:04:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm26.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=627.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re; Now we're talking</span><hr size=1> Alright that sound very decent. Its even a bit original thanks to the time setting. <br>
<br>
Now figure out where those muties have been living or how they've been hiding to keep themselves a secret for all those years. What are they capable of? Be very specific here because you don't want to go throwing in powers all helter skelter. <br>
<br>
The agency, how secret is it? How long has he been working there? Who are the people that are going to be taking even the smallest part in your story that work with him? How he treats the girl that brings coffe is a nice indicator of what kinda guy he is. Speaking of which, what kind of guy is he? How did this agency find out about it? <br>
<br>
We're still a bit of a ways from a soilid starting point for a plot yet. You need to know everything about all the characters, even if a lot won't be put into the story. Did Corbin get into a fight while he was younger that left him with a scar on his hand that gives him an itchy trigger finger? <br>
<br>
Now know your bad guys. Here are a few ideas in question form: Do these muties have their own organization? Or are they just mindlessley carrying out an order after being re-animated from cryostasis by the last scientist involved in the project who still feels Hitler is right? If the second option or something like it is the way you're going, Why were they put frozen or whatever? You may need to take a few trips back in time to explain the way they think. So remember its easier to mold well developed characters into a story than it is to make a story without knowing anything about everyone. <br>
<br>
